[
  {
    "text": "Deena Khattab: Hi, I'm Deena Khattab, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "a designer on the Apple Design team. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "Later, I'll be joined by my colleagues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jennifer and Matthew. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=7"
  },
  {
    "text": "We're really excited to talk through the process of designing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "for Apple Watch Series 7, but before we get started, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's take a quick look at what's new. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple Watch Series 7 comes in two new sizes: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "41 mm and 45 mm. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "Both watches feature larger active content areas ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "than ever before. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "The 41 mm is 176 by 215 points, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the 45 mm is 198 by 242 points. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "The display on Apple Watch Series 7 curves over the edge, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=46"
  },
  {
    "text": "featuring a subtle wraparound effect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=50"
  },
  {
    "text": "The bezel around the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=55"
  },
  {
    "text": "is thinner and less visible than ever before. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, the screen has a larger corner radius ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "than previous devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "Keeping these key hardware differences in mind, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "we identified three useful design principles ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "to shape the UI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "Series 7 has the largest content areas we've had on watch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=77"
  },
  {
    "text": "We enlarged UI components to make full use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the additional space for enhanced usability. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "We closely examined typography and color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "to create clearer hierarchy in watch apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple Watch has always been about lightweight, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=98"
  },
  {
    "text": "glanceable experiences. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "We took a look at navigation and wayfinding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "to offer a better sense of place in just a quick glance. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "In summary, apps for Apple Watch Series 7 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=111"
  },
  {
    "text": "should be larger, clearer, and more glanceable. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the next section, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jenn will talk about how you can use updated UI elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "to embody these principles in your own apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=124"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jennifer Patton: Thanks, Deena. Let's start with layout margins. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because the corners are so curved, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "content needs to come in and down ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "so it fits well in the corners. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "Status bars get taller, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "matched by a taller scroll clearance margin ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "at the bottom of the screens. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "And with the smaller bezel ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "between the active display area and the hardware casing, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "we were discerning about content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "that nears the edges of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "Layout margins are generous on Series 7 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "to give the content plenty of room to breathe.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=162"
  },
  {
    "text": "Matthew Koonce: Thanks, Jennifer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hi there, my name is Matthew. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's use Stocks as an example ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=171"
  },
  {
    "text": "of how we can use margins effectively on watchOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=173"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, let's remove the margins that are already applied. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see, this layout has a couple of issues. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a closer look. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first issue is the text for the current stock price. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's very close to the edges of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "This could be a problem on the wraparound display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "on Apple Watch Series 7. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second issue is the Nasdaq text, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is clipped by the corners of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, we've lost the text alignment ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the leading edge of the navigation bar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how we can resolve these issues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "with some SwiftUI code. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here I have a snippet from the Stocks layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is a simple VStack. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we can adjust the layout for the current price view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "by using the .scenePadding modifier. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "This modifier applies the system-defined padding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=235"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the layout margin. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=238"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "this resolves the layout for the current price view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's use the same .scenePadding modifier ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the Nasdaq text below.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "And once again, this resolves our layout issues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "and restores the alignment we were looking for. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "Note that we did not apply the modifier to the day chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "Some content, like this chart, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "is perfectly fine to go to the edges of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "Try to preserve using the .scenePadding modifier ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "only for text content that would distort ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "or be clipped by the edges of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=279"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jennifer: We brought large titles into watchOS this year ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "to make apps more glanceable, offer a better sense of place, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "and establish clearer hierarchy within apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scrolling table views will get this large title, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "similar to large titles on iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "The title transitions into the status bar on scroll. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "Root levels and subviews will get the large title. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=306"
  },
  {
    "text": "Settings is a great example of how large titles can be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "in an app to define a clear sense of place. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "In fixed views that don't scroll, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "we looked for opportunities like Timer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "to bring the title of the view into the content area ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "and out of the status bar, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=328"
  },
  {
    "text": "or just remove it entirely where it's not needed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "divorcing the titling of the view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the Back button navigation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also have fixed views where the status bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "is still the best place for titling information, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=341"
  },
  {
    "text": "like this world clock detail example. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "Large titles were particularly inspired ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the larger active content area available on Series 7 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "but they also work well on previous 40 and 44 mm devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "Matthew: SwiftUI makes it simple ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "to configure large titles for your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=365"
  },
  {
    "text": "By default on watchOS 8, all navigation titles are large ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "and are tinted by the application accent color. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=373"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you do not want a large title on a particular view, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use the .navigationBarTitleDisplayMode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=382"
  },
  {
    "text": "modifier. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "After applying this modifier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=387"
  },
  {
    "text": "any subsequent view in your hierarchy ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "will inherit the display mode of the view above.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=392"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jennifer: Color is meant to help with wayfinding, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "information hierarchy, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "and signal the personality of your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=404"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this Mindfulness example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "the teal color reinforces the app identity and experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "We use System Teal as the app key color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=414"
  },
  {
    "text": "and pushed back the System Gray platter background color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a more muted effect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "List view apps are common on watch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this Mail example, the use of blue backgrounds ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "enforces that you're in the Mail app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=431"
  },
  {
    "text": "and not another app that uses a similar navigation pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=433"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "bright yellow platters visually differentiate Tips ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "from other carousel navigation apps like Workout. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "It also reinforces the continuity ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the Tips experience across all our platforms. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "Matthew: You can configure your application's accent color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=455"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the asset catalog. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "After setting a color here, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=460"
  },
  {
    "text": "all navigation bars will automatically use this color. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "More information about configuring the accent color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be found in the developer documentation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, you can easily use the color yourself in SwiftUI ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "by using the .accentColor modifier. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Mail, we set the listItemTint ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the application's accent color at 30 percent opacity. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jennifer: We also took a close look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "at buttons and button shapes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "while designing for Series 7 watches. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "The current button system looks like this. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=497"
  },
  {
    "text": "We have rounded rectangular buttons ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are seen in scrolling views, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=502"
  },
  {
    "text": "and we have a set of pinned buttons ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are only seen in fixed views that don't scroll. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "They're pinned to the bottom of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "and meant to complement the shape of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "For Series 7, we expanded on the same basic system ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=517"
  },
  {
    "text": "of scrolling and nonscrolling buttons. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "We simplified to a common secondary-button color scheme, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "and side-by-side buttons are switching ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=529"
  },
  {
    "text": "from a split-lozenge shape to side-by-side pill shapes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=531"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here are a couple of examples of buttons in updated apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "A primary scrolling button in the Alarms list at left ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "and side-by-side buttons in the UIPickerView on the right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a closer look at these pinned button shapes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=551"
  },
  {
    "text": "We took great care in crafting the shape of the buttons ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=555"
  },
  {
    "text": "for Series 7. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=559"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's an example of what it would look like ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=561"
  },
  {
    "text": "to use a simple pill shape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=563"
  },
  {
    "text": "See how the flat plane of the button at the bottom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "creates tension with the curvature of the display? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=569"
  },
  {
    "text": "And here is the crafted button shape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=573"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll do that again. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=577"
  },
  {
    "text": "The change is subtle, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=579"
  },
  {
    "text": "but deriving the shape of the button ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=580"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the shape of the display itself ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "makes it so that these buttons that are pinned ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=585"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the bottom of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=587"
  },
  {
    "text": "and will harmonize with the hardware of the watch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "The updated buttons will go back to pre-Series 7 devices too. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=593"
  },
  {
    "text": "The height of the buttons will remain the same, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=598"
  },
  {
    "text": "so no updates to the layout should be needed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=600"
  },
  {
    "text": "for adopting these new buttons for existing UI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=603"
  },
  {
    "text": "Matthew: We've updated all buttons in SwiftUI ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=607"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the new Apple Watch Series 7 look. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=610"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the most part, this happens automatically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=614"
  },
  {
    "text": "and no changes are necessary in your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=616"
  },
  {
    "text": "That said, it's important to keep a couple things in mind. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=620"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you define a button, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=625"
  },
  {
    "text": "like the Cancel button seen here, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "SwiftUI is applying some default modifiers on your behalf. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=628"
  },
  {
    "text": "Buttons on watchOS use a bordered button style ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=634"
  },
  {
    "text": "and an automatic border shape by default. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=639"
  },
  {
    "text": "The automatic border shape means the border shape changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=644"
  },
  {
    "text": "based on context. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=647"
  },
  {
    "text": "Outside of a scroll view, the shape is a capsule. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, these Cancel and Start buttons. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=653"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the scroll view, the button has a rounded rectangle shape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, the Add Alarm button. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=662"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, there's an alternative button style ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=666"
  },
  {
    "text": "called bordered prominent. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=669"
  },
  {
    "text": "This style applies the application accent color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=671"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the button, which we do in Alarms. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=673"
  },
  {
    "text": "This gives the button a more pronounced look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "that immediately draws your attention.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=679"
  },
  {
    "text": "Deena: In this next section, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=685"
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll discuss typography updates. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=686"
  },
  {
    "text": "Series 7 uses the same default type sizes as Series 6: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=690"
  },
  {
    "text": "large for 40 mm and 41 mm ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=695"
  },
  {
    "text": "and extra large for 44 mm and 45 mm. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "As a result, we gain more character count ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=704"
  },
  {
    "text": "than previous devices.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=707"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also used type to improve accessibility ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=711"
  },
  {
    "text": "by adding three larger type sizes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=714"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's the Mail app at the default type size: extra large. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "And here it is at the new AX1, AX2, and AX3. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=722"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help those who wish to use larger type on their watch, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=730"
  },
  {
    "text": "we added Smart Type Suggestions. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=734"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the setup flow, your phone now identifies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=737"
  },
  {
    "text": "whether you have a large type setting implemented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=740"
  },
  {
    "text": "and suggests a similar type size for your new watch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=744"
  },
  {
    "text": "This feature makes it easier to use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=748"
  },
  {
    "text": "your preferred type size from the start. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=750"
  },
  {
    "text": "While focusing on typography, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=754"
  },
  {
    "text": "we recommend supplementing text labels with SF Symbols. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=756"
  },
  {
    "text": "For apps with list view-based navigation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=761"
  },
  {
    "text": "we recommend using outlined symbols ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=764"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your application's accent color, like Mail and Phone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=766"
  },
  {
    "text": "This helps with cross-platform consistency and accessibility. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=772"
  },
  {
    "text": "Align your symbol style and colors across platforms ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=778"
  },
  {
    "text": "where possible. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=781"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on SF Symbols, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=784"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out these talks from WWDC21. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=786"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we'll highlight the new keyboard ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=792"
  },
  {
    "text": "and text input features on Apple Watch Series 7. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=794"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because of the larger active screen areas, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=800"
  },
  {
    "text": "we added a full keyboard. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=803"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this keyboard designed specifically for watch, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=806"
  },
  {
    "text": "we don't draw borders around keys. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=809"
  },
  {
    "text": "This encourages swiping to type ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=812"
  },
  {
    "text": "while avoiding the feeling that you can miss a tap target. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=814"
  },
  {
    "text": "To maximize available space for typing, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=819"
  },
  {
    "text": "we pulled the delete key out of the keyboard ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=822"
  },
  {
    "text": "and into the text field. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=824"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, the keyboard allows you to customize ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=828"
  },
  {
    "text": "the autofill type for certain use cases, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=831"
  },
  {
    "text": "like passwords and two-factor authentication. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=834"
  },
  {
    "text": "Along with keyboard support, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=840"
  },
  {
    "text": "we improved functionality for text inputs. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=841"
  },
  {
    "text": "The left and right accessories can be customized ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=845"
  },
  {
    "text": "using SF Symbols. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=848"
  },
  {
    "text": "We recommend using your application's accent color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=851"
  },
  {
    "text": "for both symbols to emphasize tapability. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=854"
  },
  {
    "text": "Use descriptive words for input field placeholder text ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=860"
  },
  {
    "text": "and suggested list titles. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=864"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on the keyboard and text inputs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=867"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as how to best use them in your applications, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=871"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out these WWDC21 talks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=874"
  },
  {
    "text": "We showed you how to take advantage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=880"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the new display's full potential with scene padding, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=882"
  },
  {
    "text": "automatic button shapes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=886"
  },
  {
    "text": "and hierarchical navigation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=889"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more resources on designing for Series 7, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=892"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out \"What's new in watchOS 8\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=896"
  },
  {
    "text": "and \"What's new in SwiftUI\"\nfrom WWDC21.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-10884/?time=898"
  }
]